header: ["Judge questions VW's defense in landmark case over diesel damages"]
article content: ['KARLSRUHE, Germany (Reuters) - A German federal court judge cast doubt on Volkswagen’s (', ') reasoning after the carmaker urged the court to dismiss a claim for damages from a diesel customer.  ', 'Tuesday’s proceedings were the first time that Germany’s Federal Court of Justice, or Bundesgerichtshof, heard arguments from a plaintiff seeking damages from VW because it had sold vehicles with manipulated diesel engines.  ', 'Any ruling in this landmark case will serve as a guideline for other cases. ', 'Presiding judge Stephan Seiters said several arguments brought forward by Volkswagen were not applicable.  ', 'The case is about a Volkswagen customer who sued the company for having sold a car with a manipulated diesel engine so that it could pass emissions tests. The man had been awarded 26,000 euros in damages by a lower court. ', 'The plaintiff is seeking higher damages, while VW has asked the court to dismiss the claim altogether. ', 'A ruling will be made at a later point in time, the judge said. ', 'Reporting by Hans Seidenstuecker; writing by Thomas Seythal']
